<body>
    <h1>Spring Boot Admin Guide</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>This guide shows how to configure a spring-boot project to be mo=
nitored by <a href=3D"https://github.com/codecentric/spring-boot-admin" cla=
ss=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Spring Boot Admin</a>.</p>
<p>In order to be discovered by Spring Boot Admin and be correctly monitore=
d, you must do the following into your project:</p>
<ol>
<li>Add Consul Datastore / Service Discovery;</li>
<li>Add Zup IAM Lib;</li>
<li>Add Spring Boot Actuator Lib;</li>
<li>Configure your project to show extra info and provide actuator endpoint=
s.</li>
</ol>
<h1 id=3D"SpringBootAdminGuide-1-AddConsulDatastore/ServiceDiscovery">1 - A=
dd Consul Datastore / Service Discovery</h1>
<p>You can find the Consul guide on <a href=3D"https://zupjira.atlassian.ne=
t/wiki/spaces/RW/pages/66584583/Consul+Guide" rel=3D"nofollow">this link</a=
> (Or just look for "<a href=3D"https://zupjira.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/R=
W/pages/66584583/Consul+Guide" rel=3D"nofollow">Consul Guide</a>" on Conflu=
ence)</p>
<h1 id=3D"SpringBootAdminGuide-2-AddZupIAMLib">2 - Add Zup IAM Lib</h1>
<p>You can find the Zup IAM Lib on <a href=3D"https://zupjira.atlassian.net=
/wiki/spaces/RW/pages/51353847/Library+-+IAM" rel=3D"nofollow">this link</a=
> (Or just look for "<a href=3D"https://zupjira.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/R=
W/pages/51353847/Library+-+IAM" rel=3D"nofollow">Library - IAM</a>" on Conf=
luence)</p>
<h1 id=3D"SpringBootAdminGuide-3-AddSpringBootActuatorLib">3 - Add Spring B=
oot Actuator Lib</h1>
<p>First, you need to add this dependency on the project's web app&nbsp;<st=
rong>pom.xml</strong>.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>Actuator pom example</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">    &lt;=
dependencies&gt;
        ...
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-actuator&lt;/artifactId&g=
t;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        ....
    &lt;/dependencies&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>Then add the following into your <strong>application.properties</strong>=
:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>application.properties example</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># ... Y=
our actual config

# Actuator
management.security.enabled=3Dtrue
management.security.roles=3Dmonitoring
management.context-path=3D/manage</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Note: The <strong>context-path </strong> can be&nbsp;overwritten by the =
consul config.</p>
<p>After that, you can run your application and check if it's working by op=
ening&nbsp;<strong>http://application_host:application_port/manage/health</=
strong>. If everything is OK it should output a json with status&nbsp;<stro=
ng>UP</strong> or&nbsp;<strong>DOWN</strong>, indicating that everything is=
 working as intended.</p>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"SpringBootAdminGuide-4-Configuringyourproject">4 - Configuring yo=
ur project</h1>
<p>In order to obtain the the of your project's correct version, you must a=
dd the spring boot maven build plugin, and security actuator endpoints.</p>
<h2 id=3D"SpringBootAdminGuide-4.1-AddingtheSpringBootMavenPlugin">4.1 - Ad=
ding the Spring Boot Maven Plugin</h2>
<p>The Spring Boot Maven Plugin provides Spring Boot support in Mavne, allo=
wing you to package executable jar or war archives and run an application "=
in-place". To use it you must be using Maven 3.2 (or better). In this case,=
 we will be using the&nbsp;<strong>build-info</strong> which packages the j=
ar with some extra metadata about the application, such as Version, Build N=
umber, etc.</p>
<p><br>To include the plugin, add the following snippet on the&nbsp;<strong=
>web apps</strong> plugins section:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>pom.xml example with maven plugin</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">    &lt;=
build&gt;
        ...
        &lt;plugins&gt;
            ...
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&g=
t;
                &lt;executions&gt;
                    &lt;execution&gt;
                        &lt;goals&gt;
                            &lt;goal&gt;build-info&lt;/goal&gt;
                        &lt;/goals&gt;
                    &lt;/execution&gt;
                &lt;/executions&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
    &lt;/build&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>To test if everything is working fine, just execute&nbsp;<strong>mvn cle=
an install</strong>. After this, start your web application and check if th=
e route&nbsp;<strong>http://application_host:application_port/manage/info</=
strong> is up and running. The output must be something like the following.=
:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>Actuator info output example with maven plugin</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "build": {
    "version": "2018R1.0.0-SNAPSHOT",
    "artifact": "rw-iam-application",
    "name": "rw-iam-application",
    "group": "br.com.zup.rw",
    "time": 1515762629000
  }
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"SpringBootAdminGuide-4.2-SecuringActuatorEndpoints">4.2 - Securin=
g Actuator Endpoints</h2>
<p>This process is the same that you already did on stage 2 of this guide,&=
nbsp;<strong>Add Zup IAM Lib</strong>.</p>
<p>The difference is that you should secure the actuator endpoints. There a=
re several ways of doing it, I will show the commonest way of doing it. Be =
advised that it very restrictive as I'll be using a match-all pattern to se=
cure the whole actuator context-path. Note that you could be using some end=
points that matches actuator context-path and should handle it individually=
.</p>
<p>To secure the actuator endpoints, add the following into you&nbsp;<stron=
g>security-constraints.yml</strong> file:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>security-constraints.yml example</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">---
constraints:

    # Your applications constraints

  - pattern: /manage/{slug:^(?!health).*$}
    roles:
      monitoring:
        - GET
        - POST
        - PUT
        - DELETE
        - HEAD
        - OPTIONS
        - PATCH

  - pattern: /manage/{slug:^(?!health).*$}/**
    roles:
      monitoring:
        - GET
        - POST
        - PUT
        - DELETE
        - HEAD
        - OPTIONS
        - PATCH

publicConstraints:
  - pattern: /manage/health
    methods:
      - GET
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
